properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 8:23AM CST until February 12 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Aberdeen SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations of
up to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze. Winds
gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Stanley and Jones Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST /5 PM MST/ this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
cold wind chills as low as 25 below zero could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST /5 PM MST/ THIS EVENING
